The situation at the water works is mentioned in NYT of May 3, 1914
  <a href="http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9506EFD81E39E633A25750C0A9639C946596D6CF" rel="nofollow">query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9506EFD81E39E633A...</a>
&quot;VERA CRUZ, May 2. -- What promised to be the first fight between the United States Army and the Mexican troops to-day ended in the exchange of not more than half a dozen shots. The Mexicans had threatened to &quot;attack immediately unless the Americans surrendered their position at the water works at Tejar within ten minutes,&quot; but failed to carry out their threat. &quot;
